sentences: In addition to his solo act, he was part of rap band Forever from 1998 to 2001 under the name Money.
He appeared in collective Julma-Henri & Syrjäytyneet (2007–2010) and from 2010 strongly collaborated as duo Julma-Henri & RPK.
He appeared in collective Julma-Henri & Syrjäytyneet (2007–2010) and from 2010 strongly collaborated as duo Julma-Henri & RPK.
With RPK, he launched an official duo rap act known as Eurocrack  (stylized as E U R O C R A C K) in 2012.
Julma-Henri began his career at Forever, a rap band he formed in Oulu in 1998 under the pseudonym Money.
The band released the single "Mobmusic", a demo EP in 2000.
In 2003, cooperated with Asa and Steen1.
In 2004, he worked on Soundtrack 2 My Life as a full album with appearances by Steen1, Tasis, Travis Bicle and Afu Ra (USA) – however, the album was never released.
Julma-Henri found recognition with his debut studio album Al-Qaida Finland in 2005 while still residing in Oulu.
In 2005 and 2006, he had a joint radio show Bassoradio (a collective project of tens of DJs) with Steen 1 as Julma-Henri & Ystävät (meaning Julma-Henri & Friends)
In 2007, he appeared in a music video with Asa called "240306" (aka "RikRek").
In May 2007, Panama Rayon and Laineen Kasper reproduced and rereleased Julma-Henri's Al-Qaida Finland on Colin Records in Helsinki with great success.
In January 2008, an all-Finland "Support Al-Qaida Finland Tour" was organized assisted by a number of rap and hip hop acts.
Based on this success, he released in December 2008 the mixtape SRJTNT Vol 1 criticizing commercialization of rap.
His 2009 release Outo nauha was a split album with Laineen Kasperi.

In 2010, he released the album Psykoterapia again crediting Julma-Henri & Syrjäytyneet and dealing, as many of his earlier albums with social exclusion and mental health problems and the dark side of life.

After Psykoterapia, Julma-Henri & Syrjäytyneet assembly broke in 2010 due to disagreements and Julma-Henri proceeded on collaborations with rapper RPK (of Ceebrolistics fame) with joint Kutsu EP of 6 tracks released in December 2010 credited to Julma-Henri & RPK.

After Psykoterapia, Julma-Henri & Syrjäytyneet assembly broke in 2010 due to disagreements and Julma-Henri proceeded on collaborations with rapper RPK (of Ceebrolistics fame) with joint Kutsu EP of 6 tracks released in December 2010 credited to Julma-Henri & RPK.
The follow-up album "HENRI" with 17 tracks from Julma-Henri & RPK in February 2013 produced another music video "Pala".
In December 2011, Julma-Henri released his new album Radio Jihad... SRJTNT vol.

As early as July 2011, and prior to Radio Jihad... release by Julma-Henri, RPK announced on Bassoradio that he was collaborating with Julma-Henri on a brand new project called Eurocrack and that an album was in the offing.
In 2013, the track "Douppii douppaa" was released as pre-release in music video form in promotion of the debut studio album of Eurocrack (stylized as E U R O C R A C K).
The album titled Huume (stylized as H U U M E) was released on 28 June 2013 entering the Finnish Albums Chart at number 7 in its first week of release.

In the early 2000s, his music and public image were widely associated with anarchism and proletarian activism and he made a name for himself by performing in illegal parties, political protests and even riots.
In 2007, he appeared in a music video with Asa called "240306" (aka "RikRek").
In preparation, the two released Euro Crack EP in the July 2012.
The album titled Huume (stylized as H U U M E) was released on 28 June 2013 entering the Finnish Albums Chart at number 7 in its first week of release.
